  "texts": [
    "This strategy ensures that all image tiles have the same effective optical magnification Fig. 33Fig.3Summary of approach for tile-based deep learning models.",
    "a Image tiles are extracted from whole-slide images after any slide processing and buffered into TFRecords.",
    "During training, tiles are read from TFRecords, augmented, stain normalized, standardized, and batched.",
    "In this weakly-supervised approach, models are trained using ground-truth labels for each tile determined from the label of the corresponding slide.",
    "b When evaluating a tile-based model, image tiles do not need to be buffered into TFRecords."
  ]
}